(1505, 'LRRTM2', 'Predicted to enable neurexin family protein binding activity. Predicted to be involved in regulation of postsynaptic density assembly. Predicted to act upstream of or within several processes, including long-term synaptic potentiation; negative regulation of receptor internalization; and positive regulation of synapse assembly. Is active in GABA-ergic synapse and postsynaptic specialization membrane. [provided by Alliance of Genome Resources, May 2025]', '5', 'protein_coding', 49171898, 49175235, 54.07, 2, 'ENSG00000146006', 'O43300'),
