(3756, 'ZNF585B', 'Predicted to enable zinc ion binding activity. Predicted to be involved in regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II. Predicted to be active in nucleus. [provided by Alliance of Genome Resources, May 2025]', '19', 'miRNA', 31355224, 31355316, 59.14, 1, 'ENSG00000245680', 'Q52M93'),
(3757, 'ZNF598', 'Zinc-finger proteins bind nucleic acids and play important roles in various cellular functions, including cell proliferation, differentiation, and apoptosis. This protein and Grb10-interacting GYF protein 2 have been identified as a components of the mammalian 4EHP (m4EHP) complex. The complex is thought to function as a translation repressor in embryonic development. [provided by RefSeq, Oct 2012]', '16', 'protein_coding', 3043622, 3045747, 57.71, 4, 'ENSG00000292232', 'Q86UK7'),
